{"id":"wafers","term":"Wafers","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Thin cakes (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 16:31\">Ex. 16:31</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 29:2\">29:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 29:23\">23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 2:4\">Lev. 2:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 7:12\">7:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 8:26\">8:26</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 6:15\">Num. 6:15</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 6:19\">19</a>) used in various offerings.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 16:31","Exodus 29:2","Exodus 29:23","Leviticus 2:4","Leviticus 7:12","Leviticus 8:26","Numbers 6:15","Numbers 6:19"]}